spapers. He concludes with a treatment of the paper's fortunes during the era of the French Revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPress and politicszEuropexHistoryy18th century. 4aEurope. 4aHistory.  aGazette de Leyde, Jean Luzac, Gazette‘s history, political journalism, editorial, absolutist regimes, censorship regimes, public opinion, newspaper, publication, technology, French Revolution.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170151140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501701511423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501701511/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles